  "body": "I was having a look at a dump provided by @brunobat and I saw quite a lot of:\r\n\r\n![Screenshot from 2024-06-12 14-20-40](https://github.com/quarkusio/quarkus/assets/1279749/bb14313f-824b-4241-8b0c-4702fad1224a)\r\n\r\nI had a look at the code of `SharedOpenArchivePathTree` here: https://github.com/quarkusio/quarkus/blob/3c6e8f9962e5c2d5c29f52458a10c2abe19afae5/independent-projects/bootstrap/app-model/src/main/java/io/quarkus/paths/SharedArchivePathTree.java#L68-L110 .\r\n\r\nAnd I found something a bit suspicious as to how the `users` are counted:\r\n\r\n- We initialize `users` at `1`\r\n- We increment it in the constructor\r\n- We also increment it on every `acquire()`\r\n- When closing, we check if `decrementAndGet()` is `0`\r\n\r\nLet's take a very simple example of me just creating an instance of `SharedOpenArchivePathTree` and closing it right away:\r\n\r\n- `users` will be `2` after the constructor call\r\n- when closing and decrementing it, it will be `1` and will not be closed\r\n\r\nNow I might have missed something obvious but in that case, a comment in the code would probably be welcome.",
